ps for what to do if your garage.";i:35;s:109:"You dont want to jump right into your project before determining what is actually wrong with the garage door.";i:36;s:84:"If the cable isnt actually broken but is actually just disconnected it can be fixed.";i:37;s:98:"If this is the case open the door and reattached the cable and be sure to put it over the pulleys.";i:38;s:56:"Be sure to check for damage while reattaching the cable.";i:39;s:69:"If the cable is worn it should be replaced to prevent further issues.";i:40;s:112:"Sometimes just because the door does not close does not mean that there is something wrong with the garage door.";i:41;s:62:"Sometimes it is on the remote or the motor of the garage door.";i:42;s:85:"In some instances the cord that connects to the motor accidentally pulled causes the.";i:43;s:50:"Thats how to fix garage door cables in a nutshell.";i:44;s:56:"The next step is to go to the inside of the garage door.";i:45;s:75:"You need to check the release handle and make sure that it is on the track.";i:46;s:81:"Once you have done this check to make sure that the sensors are working properly.";i:47;s:62:"How to Reconnect Your Garage Door Opener After a Power Outage.";i:48;s:70:"First you must disconnect the garage door opener from the door itself.";i:49;s:63:"Its best to unplug the opener from its power source beforehand.";i:50;s:59:"Pull the emergency disconnect cord hanging from the opener.";i:51;s:84:"This is the only way to disconnect the opener and allows you to fully open the door.";i:52;s:74:"Garage door springs are damaged or have rust disconnected cables and gaps.";i:53;s:41:"Garage door doesnt open more than 6-inch.";i:54;s:64:"You cannot lift the garage door manually or its completely shut.";i:55;s:89:"Usually this problem occurs when the counterbalance spring of the garage door is damaged.";i:56;s:65:"You hear a grinding or squealing sound while opening your garage.";i:57;s:26:"Reconnect the Garage Door.";i:58;s:105:"After the power returns or you are ready to start using the garage door opener simply reconnect the door.";i:59;s:116:"To do that youll need to pull on the emergency release handle and press the button on the garage door opener remote.";i:60;s:90:"The openers trolley will fold back into position from where it will reconnect to the door.";i:61;s:106:"Repairing your garage door cable may seem simple but its actually a little more complicated than it looks.";i:62;s:159:"You have to use caution with this procedure because the garage door springs are under lots of pressure and can be very dangerous if disconnected the wrong way.";i:63;s:88:"Before you do any work on the cables of your garage door you should prepare for the job.";}}